 Western specialists on Bely. The essays survey Bely's major works in all genres, summarize present research on Bely, reassess critical approaches, and offer fresh interpretations. Analytic summaries of primary works make the essays fully accessible to non-Slavist readers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 4aBiography & Autobiography. 4aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / General.2bisacsh1 aAlexandrov, Vladimir E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarlson, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCassedy, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElsworth, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFleishman, Lazar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeys, Roger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaguire, Robert A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaksimov, Dmitry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalmstad, John E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalmstad, John E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSmith, G. S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150174527040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501745270423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501745270/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-al